# Installing {{ plugin_name | capitalize }} for Codex

{{ description }}.

## Prerequisites

- [Codex](https://github.com/openai/codex) installed and configured
- Git

## Installation

### macOS / Linux

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/{{ github_username }}/{{ plugin_name }}.git ~/.codex/{{ plugin_name }}

# Create the skills directory if it doesn't exist
mkdir -p ~/.agents/skills

# Symlink skills into Codex
ln -s ~/.codex/{{ plugin_name }}/skills ~/.agents/skills/{{ plugin_name }}
```

### Windows (PowerShell)

```powershell
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/{{ github_username }}/{{ plugin_name }}.git "$env:USERPROFILE\.codex\{{ plugin_name }}"

# Create the skills directory if it doesn't exist
New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path "$env:USERPROFILE\.agents\skills"

# Symlink skills into Codex
New-Item -ItemType SymbolicLink -Path "$env:USERPROFILE\.agents\skills\{{ plugin_name }}" -Target "$env:USERPROFILE\.codex\{{ plugin_name }}\skills"
```

## Verify

Confirm the symlink is in place:

```bash
# macOS / Linux
ls -la ~/.agents/skills/{{ plugin_name }}

# Windows (PowerShell)
Get-Item "$env:USERPROFILE\.agents\skills\{{ plugin_name }}"
```

You should see a symbolic link pointing to `~/.codex/{{ plugin_name }}/skills`.

## Updating

Pull the latest changes from the repository:

```bash
cd ~/.codex/{{ plugin_name }}
git pull origin main
```

## Uninstalling

### macOS / Linux

```bash
# Remove the symlink
rm ~/.agents/skills/{{ plugin_name }}

# Remove the cloned repository
rm -rf ~/.codex/{{ plugin_name }}
```

### Windows (PowerShell)

```powershell
# Remove the symlink
Remove-Item "$env:USERPROFILE\.agents\skills\{{ plugin_name }}"

# Remove the cloned repository
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force "$env:USERPROFILE\.codex\{{ plugin_name }}"
```
